Headquartered in Noida India, Path began as an IT services organization serving markets such as Finance, Insurance, Manufacturing, BPO/ITES and Utilities. Path's success allowed us to expand globally with representation in USA and Singapore. Over 31 years of experience in providing innovative customer solutions, has positioned Path to serve the IT needs of organizations. Path has seen significant growth over the last 25 years. Our corporate headquarters spans over 14,000 square feet - including a variety of departments to serve our growing customer base. Path customer experience will always be positive and rewarding. Path is leader in the mid segment IT Services Company for the last 25 years and has won various Industry Awards till now. Path is CMMI-DEV v1.3 Maturity Level 3 Certified, certified partner of Oracle & Microsoft and also having ISO 9001:2008 certification.
Working collaboratively with other areas of Compliance both within EMEA and Globally to ensure clarity and understanding of roles and responsibilities and consistency of approach

Create, test, assemble, support, and configure applications based on business needs. Recognize the performance-impacting business drivers and create software that meets those standards. Integrate technological developments into your solutions; take part in the creation of new technologies, functionality, and automation solutions, and incorporate them into already existing ones.

Manage R3 public cloud subscriptions / accounts / projects / resources / identity management / Single Sign On. Analyse resource utilisation and consumption - recommend and implement cost reduction solutions. Ensure resource creation adheres to Policy. Implement and manage role based access control (RBAC, IAM and PIM) Export and analyse reports from Azure using native Azure toolsets. Implement and manage Azure Active Directory (AAD) EndPoint Configuration Management (e.g. Intune, Jamf) and Compliance Management Configuration and ongoing compliance of multi-factor authentication (MFA) solutions. Create scripts / tooling for management of cloud identity and resources.

Define code architecture decisions to support a high-performance and scalable product Translating wireframes into high-quality code. And building products from scratch. Designing and implementing large-scale databases. Handling lifecycles of product releases in collaboration with Product Teams.

LAMP Architect position requires a motivated, enthusiastic, and pro-active engineer with an excellent 'can-do' attitude. As part of our Procurement Processing team the LAMP Architect will be responsible for development of applications and tools using a number of different programming languages such as Java and LAMP stack architectures and should also have great command on SQL. LAMP Architect will be responsible for assigned areas of the product and must ensure that individual and team deadlines are met.

We are looking for a PHP Developer/Laravel Developer with the capability to develop a fully responsive web portal (both backend and frontend). He/She must have proficiency in the development and maintenance of the website. Good leadership skills to work cohesively in the team and also manage end delivery.

We are looking for .NET Full Stack Developer with exposure in Angular/Node technologies. Candidate should have strong experience in technical and analytical skills, with an emphasis on the implementation of best practice security principles.

We are looking for a IoT developer with 5 years of experience of working on Raspberry based devices. The candidate should have hands on experience with Azure IoT Hub, Adafruit, Azure functions, etc. He/She will have good communication presentation skills along with the ability to think out of the box, recommend and implement solutions using PHP, Python, NodeJS, .NET (Core), c#, etc. This is NOT a support role. You are expected to lead the team, find solutions, and mentor your peers.

Mandatory Skills: Sound experience in Core PHP , MySQL , codeigniter , Product development exp. preferred Desired Skills: Good knowledge in any other MVC framework Job Description: Candidate should have experience in coding and eager to learn new technologies.

Develop, test, implement and maintain application software production applicaton support. Sound knowledge in Spring MVC, Hibernate, SOAP Web services and REST Web services, Micro services in Springboot.
